description._content: Catalog #: 09_01537 Title: Elwyn H. Gibbon Special Collection Photo Waco Texas Additional Information: Douglas BT-2 (on left) and Douglas BT-1 aircraft on airfield. Handwritten inscription ""The Colonel and Captain leaving us at Waco to wait for a mechanic being sent back from Dallas"", Elwyn Gibbon (b.1911 d.1942) was an American pilot who served as a pilot in the Chinese Air Force in the Foreign Volunteer Squadron. Later he served as a Vultee Aircraft Company test pilot in Karachi, India, where he died in a plane crash in 1942. Corporation Name: Douglas Aircraft Company Tags: Elwyn H.
